#### 88

**Step 1 – Convert the given data to SI units**

\[
\begin{aligned}
V &= 230.0\ \text{cm}^{3}=230.0\ \text{mL}=0.2300\ \text{L}=2.30\times10^{-4}\ \text{m}^{3} \\
P &= 97.5\times10^{3}\ \text{Pa}=9.75\times10^{4}\ \text{Pa} \\
T &= 23.1^{\circ}\text{C}=23.1+273.15=296.25\ \text{K}
\end{aligned}
\]

**Step 2 – Total moles of gas in the bulb (ideal‑gas law)**  

\[
n_{\text{tot}}=\frac{PV}{RT}
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
n_{\text{tot}}&=\frac{(9.75\times10^{4}\ \text{Pa})(2.30\times10^{-4}\ \text{m}^{3})}
{(8.314\ \text{J mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1})(296.25\ \text{K})}  \\
&=\frac{22.425\ \text{J}}{2.463\times10^{3}\ \text{J mol}^{-1}} \\
&=9.10\times10^{-3}\ \text{mol}
\end{aligned}
\]

**Step 3 – Set up the mass balance for the mixture**

Let  

\[
n_{\text{C_4H_{10}}}=x\quad\text{(moles of butane)}\\
n_{\text{C_2H_6}}=n_{\text{tot}}-x\quad\text{(moles of ethane)}
\]

Molar masses  

\[
M_{\text{butane}}=58.12\ \text{g mol}^{-1},\qquad 
M_{\text{ethane}}=30.07\ \text{g mol}^{-1}
\]

Total mass (given)  

\[
0.3554\ \text{g}=x(58.12)+\bigl(n_{\text{tot}}-x\bigr)(30.07)
\]

Solve for \(x\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
0.3554 &=30.07\,n_{\text{tot}}+x(58.12-30.07)\\
x &=\frac{0.3554-30.07\,n_{\text{tot}}}{28.05}
\end{aligned}
\]

Insert \(n_{\text{tot}}=9.10\times10^{-3}\ \text{mol}\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
30.07\,n_{\text{tot}} &=30.07(9.10\times10^{-3})=0.2736\ \text{g}\\[2mm]
x &=\frac{0.3554-0.2736}{28.05}=2.92\times10^{-3}\ \text{mol}
\end{aligned}
\]

Thus  

\[
n_{\text{butane}} = 2.92\times10^{-3}\ \text{mol}
\]

**Step 4 – Mole percent of butane**

\[
\text{Mole fraction of butane}= \frac{n_{\text{butane}}}{n_{\text{tot}}}
= \frac{2.92\times10^{-3}}{9.10\times10^{-3}} =0.321
\]

\[
\boxed{\text{Mole percent of butane}=0.321\times100\% \approx 32.1\%}
\]

